# Contribution (ai-telegram-bot)

## Branch and PR flow

- Branch from **`master`** using **`feature/<short-description>`** only (kebab-case). CI rejects other branch names (Dependabot branches are exempt).
- Open PRs **to `master`**. Keep PRs small and focused.
- Run **`./gradlew test`** locally before push; fix failures before requesting review.

## Commits

- Prefer [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/): `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `chore:`.
- One logical change per commit when practical.

## Code generation

- **Package:** `com.ai.dev.garage.bot`
- **Stack:** Java 21, Spring Boot 3, Lombok where the module already uses it.
- **Hexagonal:** domain + application (ports/services) + adapters. Keep `adapter.in.*` thin; no business rules in controllers.
- **Persistence:** respect Flyway migrations in `src/main/resources/db/migration/` — add a new versioned script for schema changes.
- **Gradle:** plugin/toolchain/explicit dependency versions — see **gradle** rule (`gradle.mdc`).

## Tests

- Details: **testing** rule (`testing.mdc`) — JUnit 5, Mockito style, `should…When…` naming for new/changed tests, parameterized/nested where helpful, prefer `eq` / captors over `any*`.
- Add or update tests for behavior changes; do not weaken coverage without reason.

## Documentation and config

- Operator-visible behavior or env changes require updates to **`README.md`** and, when relevant, **`config.example.env`** (see **documentation-structure** rule).
- No secrets in examples.

## PR description

- State what changed and why; link issues (`Fixes #n`). Call out breaking changes and migrations.
